Class MobilePhoneContract

  • java.lang.Object
    • MobilePlan.entities.MobilePhoneContract
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<MobilePhoneContract>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MonthlyContract, PrePaidCard
    public abstract class MobilePhoneContract
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<MobilePhoneContract>
    A MobilePhoneContract base class.
    Concrete sub types must implement the units and fee structure.

    • Method Detail

      • outgoingConnections

        public java.util.List<Connection> outgoingConnections()
        Get a list of all calls placed by this contract.
        Searches all connections and returns a list of those connections for which this contract is the caller (and not the callee).
        Returns:
        list of all calls made by this contract, or empty list if no outgoing calls were placed so far

      • unitsLeft

        public abstract int unitsLeft()
        Calculates the amount of units left to use.
        The number of units left is calculated using the method getUsedUnits. If there are no more units left this method returns 0. The concrete calculation is to be implemented in concrete subclasses.
        Returns:
        the number of units not used for this contract

      • additionalFee

        public abstract float additionalFee()
        Calculates any additional fee.
        The returned value is the total of the additional fees for this MobilePhoneContract. The concrete calculation is to be implemented in concrete subclasses.
        Returns:
        the total of any additional fees in EUR.

      • setImei

        public MobilePhoneContract setImei​(java.lang.String imei)
        Sets the imei number of this MobilePhoneContract.
        Invalid arguments are ignored and the object remains unchanged. The argument is invalid if it is null. This setter is intended for method chaining.
        Parameters:
        imei - the imei number to set
        Returns:
        this MobilePhoneContract

      • getUsedUnits

        public int getUsedUnits()
        Gets the number of already used units of this MobilePhoneContract.
        The used units are calculated by summing up the units of all outgoing connections currently held by this contract. A connection is outgoing if and only if the caller of the connetion is this contract.
        Returns:
        the used units
